cases #14CF37 and #14CF279 called at 1:18pm. [MK]
Defendant Ryan M Hudson in court, in custody, with Attorney Yelena O Zarwell.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
In Case #14CF279, Mr. Hudson waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
Service of Case #14CF279 Information admitted, reading waived, the charge and maximum penalties are recited.
Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " No Contest " entered on Count #1 in Case #14CF37 and in Case #14CF279; factual basis stipulated including as to prior convictions; victim rights compliance verified (ADA Shock submits the victim impact statement in case #14CF37)the Court accepts the pleas, finds Mr. Hudson guilty, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2 and #3 in case #14CF37.

--------------------------------------------------------------

On Count #1 in Case #14CF37, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Hudson on Probation for three years, with conditions:

--to serve 365 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with work-release privileges, to commence forthwith
---Mr. Hudson is required to serve this jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in his system; non-compliance will result in loss of work-release privileges without further process.
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with all recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety: no possession or consumption of alcohol; no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription 
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--to submit to random drug and alcohol screens, to be done at the discretion of the Agent
--no operation of a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license and the approval of the Agent
--to obtain/maintain fulltime employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon request
--to pay fine of $3000 plus costs= $4813
 
--to pay blood testing costs of $56.74 to the Fort Atkinson Police Department
Days credit for time already served:  8 days 

The Court orders outright (not as conditions or Probation): 
--Revocation of drivers license for 36 months
--County alcohol and drug assessment ordered
--Jefferson Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device required on any vehicle driven by the Defendant for a 36 month period  
--6 demerit points assessed
The Court indicates that it will not allow expungement of this case #14CF37.
------------------------------------------------------------------

In Case #14CF279, the Court sentences Mr. Hudson to:
--serve six months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to commence forthwith, concurrent with the conditional jail term in Case #14CF37 
--7 days credit for time already served given
 
--Mr. Hudson is required to serve this jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in his system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon request
--pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge= $518; this amount is to be entered as a civil judgment 

Felony firearm/voting prohibition warnings given. 
The Court grants expungement of Case #14CF279 if Mr. Hudson successfully completes his term of Probation in Case #14CF37.  The Court explains to Mr. Hudson that he will need to petition for expungement at the time after the Probation term ends.
